# Java

- Follow Google Java Style unless the project already has a stricter formatter.
- Keep classes focused; prefer composition and clear package boundaries over large utility classes.
- Use explicit visibility; avoid exposing mutable collections directly.
- Validate public method inputs and document nullability expectations.
- Prefer immutable value objects where practical.
- Use structured exceptions; do not catch broad `Exception` unless translating at a boundary.
